column4: Thanks, and sorry for the bother.
I'm gonna mooch back to Windows.
I hae DSL, Elive, Ubuntu Live, SLAX
All burned onto CDs. Been trying them.
When I finally do install Ubuntu, how do I choose which OS to boot?
grub and lilo are boot managers
why do you want to install a deb file?
this is either synching or merging
if there's no change to apply to the deb, then we just sync it with Debian
if there are things to change in the deb, then we merge it
come to #ubuntu-motu to talk about that
